{
  "description": "A long exposure photograph captures a small, cascading waterfall flowing over moss-covered rocks and fallen logs within a lush forest. The water appears blurred and milky white due to the slow shutter speed, contrasting with the static, dark gray and brown rocks. Tall, reddish-brown tree trunks flank the stream, their bases shrouded in shadow. The forest floor is littered with rocks and debris. Sunlight filters through the dense canopy, creating dappled lighting on the rocks and water. The overall impression is one of serene natural beauty and the peaceful flow of water through a wild landscape.",
